27 June 2008Government will on Monday, 30 June 2008, release crime statistics for the period 1 April 2007 to 31 March 2008.The briefing will include a number of presentations by police senior management, with the Minister of Safety and Security briefing the media after the presentations.Minister Nqakula will also use this opportunity to brief the media on the Justice and Crime Prevention Security Cluster Programme of Action.Details of the briefing are as follows:Date 30 June 2008 Venue Room 159, Union Buildings, Pretoria Time 11:00-14:00 (media to arrive at 10:30)NB: There will be a video link-up with Cape Town's Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town.Members of the media wishing to attend the event should forward their names for accreditation purposes, to: E-mail: bongani@gcis.gov.za Cell: 078 402 1016Enquiries Trevor Bloem Cell: 082 802 9138Hangwani Mulaudzi Cell: 082 555 3505Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)